===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|氏|日|t1=|t2=sun|ls=ic}}, or {{Han compound|氐|日|t1=|t2=sun|abb1=y}}. Hence, the twilight or nightfall is the moment in which the sun (日) lowers and goes down (氏).

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*s-mun||dark}}. Cognate with {{och-l|悶|bored; depressed}}, {{cog|bo|མུན་པ||darkness}}, {{cog|my|မှုန်||dim; gloomy}}.

